Package ca.cgjennings.apps.arkham.dialog

Interface GameComponentExplorer.GameObject

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    GameComponentExplorer.GameObjectCollection
    Enclosing class:
    GameComponentExplorer
    public static interface GameComponentExplorer.GameObject
    An interface that allows interaction with the game components being edited by the user. This is an abstraction that allows plug-ins to safely manipulate game components even if they are not linked to the SE code base at compile time.

    If your code is linked to SE at compile time, it is generally easier to use the actual objects directly.

    Author:
    Chris Jennings

      • call

        Object call​(String methodName,
            Object... arguments)
     throws InvocationTargetException
        Call one of the methods of this game component. The game component implementation will ensure that the call is made in the correct thread and that the editor (if any) is updated to reflect the changes to the component. The arguments to the method call must match the types returned by getArgumentTypes(java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        methodName - the name of the method to call
        arguments - the arguments to the method
        Returns:
        the value returned by the method, or null if it has void return type
        Throws:
        InvocationTargetException - if the underlying method throws an exception during the method call
        IllegalArgumentException - if methodName is not a valid method or if the arguments are not appropriate for the method
